The paper proposes a framework for text detection and recognition using deep learning models, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The use of shared parameters and end-to-end training also involves optimization techniques (cs.LG) and the recognition network design involves convolutional layers (cs.IR, cs.AI).
